	<text id="title" x="37" y="35" width="456" height="" autosize="H" style="WIZARD_TITLE" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE">
		<content translate="true">Recognizing Attachment</content>
	</text>
	<text id="material" x="37" y="65" width="697" height="346" autosize="" style="WIZARD_TEXT" visible="true" fx="SHOW" hidefx="HIDE" scroll="AUTO">
		<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Discussion Topic&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;As previously discussed, attachment describes the child's relationship with the parent and caregivers. By meeting their child's needs, parents and caregivers can help guide their child to develop a secure attachment.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Video &lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Watch “Safari” from the Talaris &lt;I&gt;Everyday Moments Count &lt;/I&gt;DVD. Before watching, ask the parent to try to identify which actions the parent in the video displays to create a secure attachment with his child. For more information regarding this DVD, go to the &lt;B&gt;Resource Center.&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Disscussion&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Following the video, ask the parents what they saw the parent in the video do to help encourage attachment with their child.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Possible Responses:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The parent comforted his child when he was scared. &lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The parent reassured his child by waving to him across the playground.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The parent stayed close and encouraged his child to explore his environment.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;</content>
	</text>
